<TITLE> Son of Shajahan Siraj gets another 5 years </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 10 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court Tuesday sentenced Rajib Siraj, son of former BNP minister Shajahan Siraj, to five years rigorous imprisonment in a case regarding money laundering. Judge Md Ashraf Hossain of the Special Judge's Court-5 also fined him Tk 8.78 crore, or another year behind bars in case of failure to pay the sum, and ordered authorities to confiscate assets worth Tk 8.78 crore. The fugitive Rajib already faces a total of 40 years in prison in five separate cases involving tax evasion. His sentences will take effect from the day of his surrender or arrest. bdnews24.com/p
